            "en-x-generated": "<p>To be recognised as an EIA expert, you must meet:</p><ul><li><a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36058\">general recognition conditions</a> which apply to all environmental recognitions<ul><li>in the 3 years preceding the application for the Flemish certificate of recognition, the applicant has not received a criminal conviction in a <a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/uw-overheid/verdeling-van-de-bevoegdheden/de-europese-unie-eu-de-europese-economische-ruimte-eer-het-schengengebied-en-de-eurozone\">member state of the European Economic Area</a> for breaches of environmental legislation relating to the use of the recognition</li><li>in the 2 years preceding the application for the Flemish recognition certificate, no recognition with the same object has been withdrawn from the applicant, for violation of the related obligations of that recognition.</li></ul></li><li><strong>special conditions of recognition:</strong><ul><li>be a natural person.</li><li>have at least a <strong>bachelor'</strong> s degree or an equivalent degree and<ul><li>have at least <strong>5 years' experience</strong> per requested sub-domain in collaborating in the preparation of environmental impact studies (in a period of 7 years prior to the application for recognition)</li></ul></li><li>or you must have at least a <strong>master's</strong> degree or equivalent and<ul><li>have at least <strong>3 years' experience</strong> in collaborating in the preparation of environmental impact studies per requested sub-domain (within a period of 5 years prior to the application for recognition)</li></ul></li><li><p><strong>have passed a 60-hour training course</strong> covering the subjects stipulated in <a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36635&amp;woLang=nl\">Annex 9 of the VLAREL</a>. The subjects differ depending on the discipline or sub-domain</p></li><li><p>if you apply for accreditation as an EIR expert for the Noise or Vibration sub-domain, you must hold accreditation as an <strong>environmental expert in the discipline 'Noise and vibrations'</strong> for the Noise or Vibration sub-domain.</p></li></ul></li></ul><h3>Disciplines and sub-domains</h3><p>You can apply for accreditation as an EIA expert for various <strong>disciplines</strong> and <strong>sub-domains:</strong></p><div data-table><table data-table-type=\"grid\"><thead><tr><th>Discipline</th><th>Sub-domain</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>biodiversity</td><td>no sub-domains</td></tr><tr><td>soil</td><td><ul><li>geology</li><li>pedology</li></ul></td></tr><tr><td>noise and vibrations</td><td><ul><li>noise</li><li>vibrations</li></ul></td></tr><tr><td>climate</td><td>no sub-domains</td></tr><tr><td>landscape, built heritage and archaeology</td><td><ul><li>landscape</li><li>architectural heritage</li><li>archaeology</li></ul></td></tr><tr><td>air</td><td><ul><li>air pollution </li><li>odour</li></ul></td></tr><tr><td>man</td><td><ul><li>spatial aspects</li><li>mobility</li><li>health</li></ul></td></tr><tr><td>water</td><td><ul><li>surface and wastewater</li><li>geohydrology</li><li>marine waters</li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table></div>",
            "en": "<p>To be recognised as an EIA expert, you must fulfil:</p><ul><li><a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36058\">general recognition conditions</a> that apply to all recognitions relating to the environment<ul><li>in the 3 years that precede the application for the Flemish recognition certificate, the applicant has not been convicted of a criminal offence in a <a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/en/working-enterprise-and-investment/the-countries-of-the-european-union-eu-the-european-economic-area-eea-the-schengen-area-and-the-eurozone\">member state of the European Economic Area</a>, for infringements of the environmental legislation concerning the use of the recognition.</li><li>in the 2 years that precede the application for the Flemish recognition certificate, no recognition with the same object was revoked due to infringement of the obligations associated with that recognition.</li></ul></li><li><strong>special recognition conditions:</strong><ul><li>be a <strong>natural person</strong></li><li>having obtained at least a <strong>master’s </strong>or equivalent degree<ul><li>having at least 3 years’ practical experience in collaborating on the drawing up of environmental impact reports (in a period of 5 years preceding the application for recognition)</li></ul></li><li>having obtained at least a <strong>bachelor’s </strong>or equivalent degree<ul><li>having at least 5 years’ practical experience in collaborating on the drawing up of environmental impact reports (in a period of 7 years preceding the application for recognition)</li></ul></li><li>having <strong>successfully completed a training course</strong> of 60 hours in which the subjects listed in <a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36635&amp;woLang=nl\">annex 9 of the VLAREL</a> are covered. The subjects differ depending on the discipline or the subdomain.</li><li>if you apply for recognition as EIA expert for the subdomain ‘Noise’ or subdomain ‘Vibrations’, you must be a recognised environmental expert in the ‘Noise and Vibrations’ discipline for the subdomain ‘Noise’ or subdomain ‘Vibrations’.</li></ul></li></ul><p><a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/informatie-voor-de-mer-deskundige\">More info on the obligations for recognised EIA experts</a> can be found on the Department of Environment and Spatial Development website.</p><h2><strong>Validity period and obligations </strong></h2><p>The recognition is valid for an <strong>indefinite period</strong>. As recognised EIA expert, you must meet the following obligations among others to retain your recognition:</p><ul><li>hold <strong>insurance </strong>for third-party liability, including professional liability, in connection with the use of the recognition</li><li><strong>report every change of identification data</strong> (such as address, e-mail address) immediately via <a href=\"mailto:erkenningen.omgeving@vlaanderen.be\">erkenningen.omgeving@vlaanderen.be</a></li><li>pay the <a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/vlarel-retributies\">annual fee</a> for the supervision of the recognition. The first payment is to be made in the year following the year in which you obtained the Flemish recognition certificate. Failure to pay the annual fee will lead to automatic suspension of the recognition following a formal notice of default. If the fee is not paid within 30 days of the suspension, the recognition will automatically lapse.</li></ul>",
